課程概述 Course Description
       1 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    ~Nonlinear modeling of power conversion circuits using discrete and average techniques. Analysis and design of voltage mode and current mode control; parallel module operation and system interactions; distributed power systems; time domain simulation and frequency domain measurement techniques.    

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1DC and Steady State Analysis of PWM Converters2DC and Steady State Analysis of PWM Converters3DC and Steady State Analysis of PWM Converters4Small-signal Analysis of PWM Converters5Small-signal Analysis of PWM Converters6Small-signal Analysis of PWM Converters7Single-Loop Control for PWM Converters8Single-Loop Control for PWM Converters9Single-Loop Control for PWM Converters10Analysis of Current Mode Control Systems11Analysis of Current Mode Control Systems12Analysis of Current Mode Control Systems13Voltage Regulator Module Modeling and Control14Voltage Regulator Module Modeling and Control15Voltage Regulator Module Modeling and Control16Advanced Applications of Current Mode Control17Advanced Applications of Current Mode Control18Advanced Applications of Current Mode Control 

